{
  "text": "Detrusor SMCs hypertrophy represents the most relevant morphological alteration occurring in BOO patients. Gilpin et al. compared the morphological and morphometric characteristics of detrusor specimens from patients with unequivocal urodynamic BOO accompanied by evidence of severe bladder trabeculation at cystoscopy and subjects with normal urodynamic assessment and absent trabeculation [CITATION_1] . Although authors did not find morphological evidences of SMCs hyperplasia, the mean profile [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Of note, the evidence of SMCs hypertrophy has not been confirmed in all patients.",
